Someone came to repair my kitchen floor, so I'll pretend to still have a job and work remotely while reviewing Too Hot to Handle.
If I can only open this damned file. (OneDrive, you're a pain in the ass.)
*pirate voice* I'm here.
And that's where it starts to drill really hard. Great!
His passive-aggressive way of turning my air purifier to full capacity makes me uncomfortable, but it smells like wood shavings, so it's justified even if it's an anti-mask. And besides, I really need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
The positive point is that I've finished re-reading chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but big suspense. Good work.
In the process of searching and replacing … ➡️  the ellipsis character, and there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But okay, I'll stick with it. The most natural speeches are usually fragmented, especially when people let their emotions get the better of them.
The craftsman is vacuuming, with a bit of luck, he'll be finished soon.
He's gone (according to what I hear) to cut something. So I took a look to see where he's at. It's far from being finished :(
More than 7 pages on chapter five. That remains my favorite chapter, and it's quite polished. A few layout adjustments, and minor changes to switch to the active voice and improve concision. However, I'd love a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still tinkering in my kitchen.
He's started vacuuming again. I hope that's a good sign.
The craftsman has left!
He told me he had made an estimate for the entire floor, but the owners were being stingy and only paid for the small damaged area near the door. That's much better.
The house is airing out, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I enjoy a cup of tea in the garden!
